==English==

===Etymology===
{{back-form|en|inflammable}}, which is used to avoid confusion with {{m|en|non-flammable}}, as the prefix ''[[in-#Etymology 2|in-]]'' could be mistakenly thought to mean "un-; non-", while in fact, it is rather closely related to {{m|en|en-}}.

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# Capable of burning, especially a liquid.
# Easily set on fire.
# Subject to easy [[ignition]] and rapid [[flaming]] [[combustion]].

====Synonyms====
* {{l|en|inflammable}}

====Antonyms====
* {{l|en|non-flammable}}, {{l|en|nonflammable}}

